    • Method Detail

      • resetExpirationTimer

        protected boolean resetExpirationTimer(long expirationTimeMillis)
        Helper method to reset the expiration timer and set it ahead by the specified amount of time in milliseconds. Removes all expiration messages from the Handler queue and adds a new message to be processed after the specified amount of time has elapsed.
        Parameters:
        expirationTimeMillis - The new expiration time in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        True if the timer was reset.

      • stopExpirationTimer

        protected void stopExpirationTimer()
        Helper method to stop the expiration timer. Removes all expiration messages from the Handler queue.

      • expire

        public void expire(boolean notify)

        >Explicitly expire the token.

        Subclass implementations should call this superclass method to notify listeners that the token has been expired. Otherwise, listeners will not be notified.

        Specified by:
        expire in interface ExpirationToken
        Parameters:
        notify - If true, the registered ExpirationListener's onExpired method will be called.

      • doExecuteOnExpiredByTimeout

        protected abstract void doExecuteOnExpiredByTimeout()
        This is executed when the token expires due to timeout. This will be executed prior to the ExpirationListener callback being invoked.
